Objectively, it is a good platform for basic and quick editing.

Best photo editing app I have ever used on a smart phone or tablet. I would dare say that the raw power of the Note 8 married with the acuity/dexterity of the S Pen and combined with Photo Editor's exhaustive image processing capabilities allows a much more intuitive and precise way to edit photos t...Full ReviewBest photo editing app I have ever used on a smart phone or tablet. I would dare say that the raw power of the Note 8 married with the acuity/dexterity of the S Pen and combined with Photo Editor's exhaustive image processing capabilities allows a much more intuitive and precise way to edit photos than what even the vast majority of home PCs can offer. Photo Editor is perfect whether your pics need a quick touch-up or an all together all-over awe-inspiring transformation. Shape and Brush tools allow you to select where you wish to edit with pixel-by-pixel precision (or broad strokes at varying hardness settings) and every tool has sliders to adjust the intensity of the edits. For a mobile app the scale and flexibility to insert layers of images and text is bar-none, including importing .otf and .tff files for custom fonts. The sheer amount of options may be intimidating at first, but as you play around you soon learn the ropes and discover endless possibilities. I could praise Photo Editor all day, actually I have before, so really just download it.
